

CuraLive

Module 31: Live Q&A Intelligence Engine

Technical Build Brief — March 2026 (Updated)



CIPC Patent App ID 1773575338868 | CIP5 Submission | Claims 46–55 | FIG 28–30

CONFIDENTIAL



1. Executive Summary

Module 31 — the Autonomous Live Q&A Intelligence Engine — is fully built and integrated into Shadow Mode. It enables real-time attendee question submission during investor events, with AI-powered triage, multi-jurisdictional compliance screening, AGI-powered autonomous tooling, and operator management through a purpose-built console.

The operator never leaves the existing Shadow Mode console. A "Live Q&A" tab gives full control over every question with one-click actions, AI-powered triage, compliance risk indicators, auto-draft responses, speaker communication, IR team chat, and blockchain-certified Clean Disclosure Certificates.

Core stack: React 19 + tRPC + Ably real-time + GPT-4o-mini + MySQL/Drizzle

Status: BUILT & DEPLOYED — 2,611 lines across 9 core files + 70 lines schema

Platform: company.curalive.app

2. Architecture Overview

The system follows a three-tier architecture connecting attendees, the AI triage engine, and operators through real-time channels:

Attendee Device --> /qa/:accessCode --> submitQuestion --> LiveQaTriageService (GPT-4o-mini)
      |
      v
live_qa_questions + live_qa_compliance_flags --> AI triage + scoring
      |
      v
Ably Channel (curalive-qa-{sessionId}) <--> Operator Console (Shadow Mode)
      | qa.submitted / qa.statusChanged --> QuestionCard + PredictiveSidebar
                                    Approve / Reject / Bot / Legal / Send to Speaker

      AGI Layer:
      AgiComplianceService --> Predictive risk analysis + auto-policy generation
      AgiToolGeneratorService --> Autonomous micro-tool creation from session patterns

3. Database Schema (5 Tables)

Migration script: scripts/create-live-qa-tables.ts

live_qa_sessions

Column	Type	Description
id	INT AUTO_INCREMENT PK	Session ID
session_code	VARCHAR(20) UNIQUE	8-char access code (e.g., KV3N8P2Q)
shadow_session_id	INT	Links to Shadow Mode session
event_name	VARCHAR(500)	Event title
client_name	VARCHAR(255)	Client/company name
qa_session_status	ENUM	active / paused / closed
total_questions	INT	Running count
total_approved	INT	Running count
total_rejected	INT	Running count
created_at	TIMESTAMP	Session creation
closed_at	TIMESTAMP	When closed


live_qa_questions

Column	Type	Description
id	INT AUTO_INCREMENT PK	Question ID
session_id	INT	FK to session
question_text	TEXT	The question
submitter_name	VARCHAR(200)	Optional (null if anonymous)
submitter_email	VARCHAR(255)	Optional (null if anonymous)
submitter_company	VARCHAR(200)	Optional (null if anonymous)
question_category	ENUM	financial / operational / esg / governance / strategy / general
question_status	ENUM	pending / triaged / approved / answered / rejected / flagged
upvotes	INT	Attendee upvote count
triage_score	FLOAT	AI urgency/relevance score (0–100)
triage_classification	VARCHAR(32)	high_priority / standard / low_priority / duplicate / hostile
triage_reason	TEXT	AI explanation of classification
compliance_risk_score	FLOAT	Regulatory risk (0–100)
priority_score	FLOAT	Combined queue priority (0–100)
is_anonymous	BOOLEAN	Submitter chose anonymous
operator_notes	TEXT	Operator-written notes
created_at	BIGINT	Unix ms timestamp
updated_at	BIGINT	Unix ms timestamp

Indexes: session_id, question_status, priority_score


live_qa_answers

Column	Type	Description
id	INT AUTO_INCREMENT PK	Answer ID
question_id	INT	FK to question
answer_text	TEXT	Response content
is_auto_draft	BOOLEAN	Generated by AI
auto_draft_reasoning	TEXT	AI reasoning for the draft
approved_by_operator	BOOLEAN	Operator approved this draft
answered_at	BIGINT	Unix ms timestamp


live_qa_compliance_flags

Column	Type	Description
id	INT AUTO_INCREMENT PK	Flag ID
question_id	INT	FK to question
jurisdiction	VARCHAR(50)	ZA_JSE / US_SEC / UK_FCA / EU_ESMA / global
risk_score	FLOAT	0–100
risk_type	VARCHAR(100)	material_non_public / forward_looking / insider_trading / selective_disclosure / market_manipulation
risk_description	TEXT	Explanation
recommended_action	ENUM	forward / route_to_bot / legal_review / delay_24h
auto_remediation_suggestion	TEXT	Safe alternative wording
resolved	BOOLEAN	Operator resolved the flag
created_at	TIMESTAMP	Flag creation


live_qa_platform_shares

Column	Type	Description
id	INT AUTO_INCREMENT PK	Share ID
session_id	INT	FK to session
platform	ENUM	zoom / teams / webex / meet / generic
share_type	ENUM	link / embed / widget
share_link	VARCHAR(1000)	Generated share URL
white_label	BOOLEAN	White-labelled (no CuraLive branding)
brand_name	VARCHAR(255)	Custom brand name
brand_color	VARCHAR(7)	Custom brand hex colour
click_count	INT	Tracking clicks
created_at	TIMESTAMP	Share creation


4. Backend API — tRPC Router (liveQa.*)

File: server/routers/liveQaRouter.ts (596 lines)

Auth: All operator endpoints use operatorProcedure (requires operator or admin role). Public endpoints use publicProcedure.

Operator Endpoints (require login + operator role)

Endpoint	Type	Description
liveQa.createSession	Mutation	Create Q&A session linked to Shadow Mode. Returns session with 8-char access code
liveQa.getSession	Query	Get session by ID
liveQa.getSessionByShadow	Query	Get Q&A session linked to a Shadow Mode session
liveQa.updateSessionStatus	Mutation	Set session to active / paused / closed
liveQa.listQuestions	Query	List questions with answer count + unresolved compliance flags. Filterable by status
liveQa.updateQuestionStatus	Mutation	Set question status + optional operator notes. Publishes Ably event
liveQa.generateDraft	Mutation	AI-generate a compliance-safe draft response (GPT-4o-mini) with AGI compliance verification pass
liveQa.submitAnswer	Mutation	Submit operator response, mark as answered. Publishes Ably event
liveQa.getAnswers	Query	List all answers for a question
liveQa.getComplianceFlags	Query	List compliance flags for a question
liveQa.resolveComplianceFlag	Mutation	Mark a compliance flag as resolved
liveQa.listSessions	Query	List all Q&A sessions
liveQa.sendToSpeaker	Mutation	Forward question to speaker with AI-suggested response via Ably (qa.sentToSpeaker)
liveQa.broadcastToTeam	Mutation	Urgent broadcast to speaker/IR/legal team via Ably (qa.teamBroadcast)
liveQa.postIrChatMessage	Mutation	Post message to IR team chat via Ably (qa.irChat)
liveQa.generateQaCertificate	Mutation	Generate SHA-256 hash-chained Clean Disclosure Certificate for session
liveQa.generateAgiTools	Mutation	Generate autonomous micro-tools from session patterns via AGI Tool Generator
liveQa.predictiveRisk	Mutation	AGI predictive compliance risk analysis across jurisdictions


Public Endpoints (no auth — attendee-facing)

Endpoint	Type	Description
liveQa.getSessionByCode	Query	Get session info by access code (limited fields)
liveQa.submitQuestion	Mutation	Submit question with AI triage. Auto-flags if compliance risk > 70
liveQa.listQuestionsPublic	Query	List approved/triaged/answered questions (hides pending/rejected)
liveQa.upvoteQuestion	Mutation	Upvote with rate limiting (10s cooldown per fingerprint)


Real-Time Events (Ably)

Channel: curalive-qa-{sessionId}

Event	Trigger	Payload
qa.submitted	New question submitted	questionId, text, category, triageScore, complianceRiskScore, status
qa.statusChanged	Status updated (approve/reject/flag/answer)	questionId, newStatus, operatorNotes, timestamp
qa.sentToSpeaker	Question forwarded to speaker	questionId, text, suggestedResponse, category
qa.teamBroadcast	Urgent broadcast to team	message, urgency, timestamp
qa.irChat	IR team chat message	message, sender, timestamp


5. AI Triage Service

File: server/services/LiveQaTriageService.ts (162 lines)

Model: GPT-4o-mini via invokeLLM

triageQuestion()

Analyses each submitted question and returns:

category: financial / operational / esg / governance / strategy / general
triageScore: 0–100 (urgency/relevance)
triageClassification: high_priority / standard / low_priority / duplicate / hostile
triageReason: Natural language explanation
complianceRiskScore: 0–100 (regulatory risk)
priorityScore: 0–100 (combined queue ordering)
complianceFlags[]: Per-jurisdiction flags with risk type, recommended action, and auto-remediation suggestion

Jurisdictions screened: ZA_JSE, US_SEC, UK_FCA, EU_ESMA, global

Risk types detected: material_non_public, forward_looking, insider_trading, selective_disclosure, market_manipulation

generateAutoDraft()

Generates a compliance-safe draft response:

Under 200 words
Avoids forward-looking statements
Includes appropriate disclaimers
Flags if management/legal input needed
Runs AGI compliance verification pass (AgiComplianceService) across all four jurisdictions before returning
Returns answerText + reasoning + compliance verification result

6. AGI Services Layer

File: server/services/AgiComplianceService.ts (182 lines)

Predictive risk analysis engine that operates across ZA_JSE, US_SEC, UK_FCA, and EU_ESMA jurisdictions.

predictiveRiskAnalysis()

Analyses session context and returns:
riskLevel: low / medium / high / critical
jurisdictionAlerts[]: Per-jurisdiction risk indicators with confidence scores
policyRecommendations[]: Auto-generated policy suggestions based on session patterns
complianceScore: 0–100 (overall session compliance health)

verifyComplianceResponse()

Pre-screens draft responses before they reach the operator:
Checks for forward-looking statements
Validates against selective disclosure rules
Ensures proper disclaimer language
Returns pass/fail with remediation suggestions

File: server/services/AgiToolGeneratorService.ts (121 lines)

Autonomous micro-tool generation from live session patterns.

generateTools()

Analyses session question patterns and proposes:
toolName: Descriptive name for the micro-tool
toolDescription: What it does and why it's useful
triggerCondition: When the tool should activate
estimatedImpact: Expected benefit to the operator
category: compliance / analytics / communication / workflow

7. Platform Embed Service

File: server/services/PlatformEmbedService.ts (256 lines)

Generates share links, embed codes, and event summaries for distributing the Q&A session across platforms.

generateShareLink(): Creates platform-specific share URLs (Zoom, Teams, WebEx, Meet, generic)
generateEmbedCode(): Creates embeddable widget HTML for integration into external pages
generateEventSummary(): Creates shareable event summary with session statistics
White-label support: Custom brand name and colour for client-facing links

8. Operator Console UI

File: client/src/components/LiveQaDashboard.tsx (931 lines)

Tab: "Live Q&A" in Shadow Mode (8th tab)

Top Bar

Event title + session code
Live question count
Share Link button (copies /qa/{code} to clipboard)
Pause Q&A / Resume Q&A toggle
End Q&A button
Show/Hide Insights toggle

Question Cards

Each question renders as a QuestionCard with:

Triage Score Badge: HIGH (red) / MED (amber) / LOW (green) with numeric priority
Status Badge: Pending / Triaged / Approved / Answered / Rejected / Flagged
Category Badge: financial / operational / esg / governance / strategy / general
Compliance Risk Indicator: GREEN (clear) / AMBER (medium) / RED (high risk)
Submitter Info: Name, company (hidden if anonymous)
AI Triage Reason: Explanation from the triage engine
Upvote Count and Unresolved Compliance Flags count

One-Click Actions

Button	Action	Effect
Approve	Sets status to approved	Question visible to attendees, ready for speaker
Route to Bot	Generates AI draft + sets approved	Opens answer panel with pre-filled AI response
Legal Review	Sets status to flagged	Adds operator note "Escalated for Legal Review"
Reject	Sets status to rejected	Removes from attendee view
Generate AI Draft	Calls generateDraft	Opens answer panel with AI-generated response
Respond	Expands answer panel	Operator types/edits response, submits
Send to Speaker	Forwards question via Ably	Question sent to speaker with AI-suggested response

IR Team Chat Panel

Real-time message log for operator-to-team communication
Message input with send button
Messages published via Ably (qa.irChat event)
Broadcast to Team button for urgent messages across all channels

Blockchain Certificate Panel

Generate Clean Disclosure Certificate for the session
Displays session grade (A/B/C/D based on compliance scores)
SHA-256 hash chain showing integrity of the certificate
Chain length and hash values displayed
JSON download of the full certificate for audit trail

Predictive Sidebar

Panel	Content
Session Analytics	Total questions, approved count, flagged count, average triage score
Live Sentiment	Real-time compliance risk level (Positive/Neutral/Cautious) with risk bar
Materiality Heatmap	Category distribution with proportional bars
Anticipated Questions	Top 5 predicted analyst questions with match detection



9. Attendee Q&A Interface

File: client/src/pages/AttendeeQA.tsx (274 lines)

Route: /qa/:accessCode — public, no login required, mobile-friendly

Live event header with session status indicator (pulsing green = live)
Question submission form (textarea + optional name/company/email + anonymous toggle)
Character limit: 5–2,000 characters
Voice-to-Text: Microphone button using Web Speech API for hands-free question submission (useRef-based recognition control)
Real-time question list (5s polling) showing approved/triaged/answered questions
Upvote button per question (local dedup via votedIds state)
Category badges and "Answered" status indicator
Paused/Closed session messaging with appropriate UI states
Footer: "Powered by CuraLive"

10. Security Model

Layer	Implementation
Operator auth	All operator endpoints use operatorProcedure (requires operator or admin role)
Public endpoints	submitQuestion, listQuestionsPublic, getSessionByCode, upvoteQuestion only
Upvote abuse prevention	10-second cooldown per fingerprint, auto-purge of stale entries
Insert ID safety	Uses MySQL insertId from INSERT result (no race condition)
SQL injection	All dynamic queries use parameterized conn.execute(query, params)
Data exposure	Public list only shows triaged/approved/answered questions (hides pending/rejected/flagged)
Anonymous submissions	Name, company, AND email all nulled at insert time when isAnonymous = true
Share link integrity	Session ID + code integrity check in share link generation
Response rate accuracy	Auto-drafts excluded from response rate calculations

11. Connection Flow (15-Second Start)

1. Operator logs into company.curalive.app
2. Goes to Shadow Mode tab
3. Clicks Live Q&A tab
4. Clicks Launch Live Q&A Session (auto-links to active Shadow Mode session)
5. System generates 8-char session code and creates Q&A session
6. Operator clicks Share Link — copies company.curalive.app/qa/KV3N8P2Q to clipboard
7. Sends link to attendees via chat/email/meeting chat
8. Questions flow in with AI triage in real-time

No extra logins. No separate apps. No platform dependencies.

